@Eric Hougland is one of the people you really need to appreciate (N. B. I am not one of them).

You might consider that it is almost impossible to see variations in verb tense.  I could see "sit" when "sat" is actually right.  Very, very hard to see these kinds of errors with a fuzzy logic brain, which is what we are all using.

Think of one of those passages when you just could not see (nor would anyone see) the duplicated "the".

We have brains that fill in gaps.  That's probably why we're so successful as a species (on a relative evaluation).  

But it really plays havoc with out ability to find errors in crosswords.

